The paper proposes a novel AI method for detecting political bias in long text content using universal sentence encoders and other existing methods. This suggests a focus on natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also addresses the issue of domain adaptation, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's general applicability to other settings suggests a potential fit with the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
